Quote:   [Marlborough] ... - the grass land [near Kaikoura] gave place to bushes, grass, and scrub, - the frequent patches of black birch on the sides of the hills told of inferior soil and a greater height above sea level; ...
Notes:  1851 Jan Weld Letter in 1851 Feb 21 NZGG 30



