Edition:
Quote:  In some places a few patches of black birch are found in the gullies, and manuka scrub on the ranges; but towards the Manuherikia only a few patches of matakaru, and a dark small-leaved shrub are to be met with.
Notes:  c1857 Alex Garvie [Report on Otago] in 1947 Beattie Early Runholding 19



