Date:  0/0/1875
Source:  Adventuring in Maoriland in the Seventies
Author:  MEREDITH
Vol / Page:  33
Edition:  1935
Quote:  But the black birch of this country [Wairarapa] takes the cake for toughness and shortness of grain and stem. It is tough to fall and tough to saw, and ... it has to be blasted with powder to get a crack in it to put a wedge in.
Notes:  c1872 in c1875 Meredith Adventuring in Maoriland (1935) 33

