Quote:  The wood ... is from that variety of Fagus termed emphatically by the colonists [of Nelson] the <i>Black-</i>Birch, a tree with a sooty rough stem, and minute heart-shaped leaves, growing at low levels.
Notes:  (Monro)

Date:  0/0/1869
