Vol / Page:  1/iii/32
Edition:
Quote:  Red Birch of Otago, Black Birch of Nelson, Beech, etc. (<i>Fagus Menziesi</i>), a valuable timber tree, found from the sea level to 4000 feet altitude, sometimes attaining a diameter of 12 feet. ... Black Birch of Otago, Beech, etc. (<i>Fagus fusca</i>), another valuable timber tree, attaining a great size; ...
Notes:  (Buchanan Botany Otago)
